		<div id="comment_body_64391654"><p>The oceans already do this.  It's more accurate to say these are aerosolized saltwater droplets.  The clouds have water vapor but on contact with these droplets, it will pull water out of the air into the droplets.  Bigger water droplets scatter and reflect more light - the cloud turns white.</p><p>It wouldn't be a high enough concentration of salt to matter compared to the water already in the clouds, but doing it over the ocean is a perfectly reasonable location anyway, with the supply of limitless brine for the<span class="substr"> </span></p></div>
